Key Match Events: Travis Head scored an unbeaten 154* from 129 balls
Marnus Labuschagne took 3 wickets for 39 runs
Adam Zampa took 3 wickets for 49 runs
Australia won by 7 wickets with 36 balls remaining
Post-Match Reflections: Ben Duckett expressed self-admonishment after giving away an international century for the second time in a month
Travis Head's innings was the fundamental reason why Australia overcame the odds and won the match
Miscellaneous Highlights: Ben Dwarshuis was forced to leave the field after just four overs with a strained pectoral muscle
Marnus Labuschagne and Adam Zampa combined to claim 9 wickets for 190 runs in 30.4 overs
Australia's spinners claimed 10 sixes compared to England's 8 sixes
